The paper deals with the problem of tracking and identifying objects in a dynamic environment, which is a common problem in computer vision and robotics. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.RO (Robotics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel approach using expectation-maximization methods, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, hence cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of tracking objects in a noisy and incomplete environment, which is a common problem in control systems, hence cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a likely sub-category.
